cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.DM, cs.CE, cs.NI

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a local search algorithm that exploits data structures to solve the MinVC problem.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as local search is a common technique in AI and the paper proposes an algorithm to find optimal or near-optimal solutions.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the MinVC problem is a well-known NP-hard problem in discrete mathematics.
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is possible as the paper discusses solving the MinVC problem on real-world massive graphs, which could be relevant to computational science and engineering.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is less likely but still possible as the MinVC problem can be applied to network optimization and the paper discusses experimental results on a wide range of real-world graphs.
